marc21:datafield.marc21:subfield: Angelica Archipenko photograph album documenting travels through the United States and Canada

Album includes photos and postcards from various sites across the U.S. and Canada, including Niagara Falls, the Southwest and California.
Aside from sights and scenery, photographs depict friends and locals, including many Native Americans.
Photos are annotated in German by Archipenko.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
